60|$|May did not answer. With {{her face}} hid {{in her hands}} {{she sat on the}} <b>edge</b> <b>of</b> <b>her</b> <b>bed,</b> weeping at the thought of her lover's fallen condition. Poor May! People said that telegraphic work was too hard for her, because her cheeks were losing the fresh bloom that she had brought from the west of Ireland, and the fingers with which she {{manipulated}} the keys so deftly were growing very thin. But sorrow {{had more to do with}} the change than the telegraph had.|$|E
