5000|$|Munch's {{painting}} Puberty {{depicts a}} young naked girl {{sitting on the}} <b>edge</b> <b>of</b> a <b>bed.</b> <b>Her</b> legs are pressed together. She holds her hands in front <b>of</b> <b>her</b> body; one lies between her knees, while the other rests on her right thigh. She stares straight ahead with eyes wide open. Her mouth is closed and her long hair hangs down over the shoulders. The light enters from the left, and behind her a dark, ominous shadow is visible. The motif is often regarded {{as a symbol of}} anxiety and fear, a young girl's awakening sexuality and the changes a young person experiences physically and psychologically on the path towards adulthood.|$|R
